          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 74</h1><p><strong>Questions 21 - 25</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B</strong> or <strong>C</strong>.</p><p>21 What do George and Lisa say about the research question given by the tutor?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    They would like to change it slightly.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    They need to decide how to interpret it.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    They find it hard to be sure of the exact wording.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>22 How does George feel about the workload for the project?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    anxious about meeting the deadline</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    pleased that Lisa will be contributing her ideas</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    confident that, as a small group, they will be productive</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>23 Lisa is against studying how people’s fitness has changed because</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    it would be irrelevant.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    the tutor has told them not to.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    getting data about this would be difficult.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>24 What concern does George have about conducting interviews with gym users?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    It could take too much time.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Their answers may not be accurate.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    They may be unwilling to be interviewed.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>25 When Lisa talks about the skills George has, she is trying to</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    reassure him that he can do well.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    advise him how to get a good mark.</td><td></td></tr><tr